#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can configure <guilabel>FTP Options</guilabel> here. At present there is "
"just two options:"
msgstr "Ovde možete podesiti i opcije FTP‑a. Trenutno postoje samo dve:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable passive mode (PASV)"
msgstr "Uključi pasivni režim"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Passive &FTP; is often required when you are behind a firewall. Many "
"firewalls only permit connections that were initiated from <quote>the "
"inside</quote>. Passive &FTP; is controlled by the client, which makes it "
"usable through firewalls."
msgstr ""
"Pasivni FTP često je neophodan kad ste iza mrežnog zaštitnog zida. Mnogi "
"zaštitni zidovi dopuštaju samo povezivanja potekla „iznutra“. Pasivnim "
"FTP‑om upravlja klijent, što ga čini upotrebljivim kroz zaštitne zidove."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mark partially uploaded files"
msgstr "Označi delimično otpremljene fajlove"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a mark is placed in this box, partially uploaded files will have a "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.part</literal> extension added to the end of "
"the file. This extension is removed once the file download is complete."
msgstr ""
"Ako je ova kućica popunjena, delimično otpremljeni fajlovi dobiće nastavak "
"<literal role=\"extension\">.part</literal> na kraju imena. Nastavak se "
"uklanja kad se završi preuzimanje fajla."

#~ msgid "timeouts"
#~ msgstr "prekovreme"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Here you can set timeout values. You might want to tweak them if your "
#~ "connection is very slow, but the default settings are appropriate for "
#~ "most users."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Ovde možete podesiti vrednosti prekovremenâ. Da ih naštelujete možete "
#~ "poželeti ako vam je veza vrlo spora, mada podrazumevane postavke "
#~ "odgovaraju većini korisnika."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Here <guilabel>Timeout Values</guilabel> are the length of time an "
#~ "application should wait for an answer from a network operation."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<guilabel>Vrednosti prekovremena</guilabel> određuju najduže vreme koje "
#~ "programi treba da čekaju na odgovor od mrežnog postupka."

#~ msgid "You can configure the following timeouts:"
#~ msgstr "Možete podesiti sledeća prekovremena:"

#~ msgid "Socket read:"
#~ msgstr "Čitanje soketa:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Some applications use <firstterm>sockets</firstterm> to communicate. You "
#~ "can think of a socket as a water tap; while it is open, water (or in our "
#~ "case, data) comes out, without any interaction. If something stops this "
#~ "flow of data, the application will wait for more to come. This could be a "
#~ "very long time, but you can configure a maximum time for an application "
#~ "to wait with this option."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Neki programi komuniciraju preko <firstterm>soketâ</firstterm>. Soket "
#~ "možete zamisliti kao slavinu za vodu: dok je odvrnuta, voda (u našem "
#~ "slučaju podaci) teče, bez ikakvog uplitanja spolja. Ako nešto zaustavi "
#~ "protok, program će čekati da stigne još podataka. To može biti veoma dugo "
#~ "vreme, ali ovom opcijom možete podesiti najduže koliko program zaista "
#~ "treba da čeka."

#~ msgid "This setting will only apply to &kde; applications, of course."
#~ msgstr "Naravno, ova postavka će imati dejstva samo na KDE programe."

#~ msgid "Proxy connect:"
#~ msgstr "Povezivanje proksija:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Sets how long to wait for a connection to a proxy server, if one is "
#~ "configured."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Zadaje koliko se čeka na vezu ka proksi serveru, ako je neki podešen."

#~ msgid "Server connect:"
#~ msgstr "Povezivanje servera:"

#~ msgid "Sets how long to wait for a connection to a remote server."
#~ msgstr "Zadaje dužinu čekanja na vezu ka udaljenom serveru."

#~ msgid "Server response:"
#~ msgstr "Odgovor servera:"

#~ msgid "Sets how long to wait for a reply from a remote server."
#~ msgstr "Zadaje dužinu čekanja na odgovor od udaljenog servera."
